snippet: Two American astronauts did quick work on Sunday as the International Space Station continued to be upgraded so that it could welcome more commercial vehicles.
abstract: American astronauts Capt Barry E Wilmore and Col Terry W Virts complete third spacewalk in eight days, part of preparations for arrival of more commercial spacecraft at International Space Station.
lead_paragraph: Two American astronauts did quick work on Sunday as the International Space Station continued to be upgraded so that it could welcome more commercial vehicles.

headline.main: Spacewalk Prepares Station for More Visits
